{"article_id":"GGQhoxKI3Nl8Siyz","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"President Obama ' s visit to Israel , the West Bank , and Jordan this week is scheduled to include more than five hours of meetings with Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu ,","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"as the president seeks to reduce tensions with the leader of America ' s closest Middle East ally on issues","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"ranging from Iran to peace with the Palestinians .","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"But the trip ,","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"which begins Wednesday morning","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"when Mr. Obama lands in Tel Aviv ,","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"is also about repairing relations with another audience","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"that will be key to the president ' s prospects","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"for advancing important regional goals for his second term :","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"the Israeli public .","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"\" This trip is very much focused on the public diplomacy side","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"[ of relations with Israel ] , much less on the hard substance , \"","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"says Natan Sachs , an expert in Israeli foreign policy at the Brookings Institution in Washington .","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"The White House is calling a speech","depth":11},{"id":14,"text":"Obama will give to the Israeli public","depth":12},{"id":15,"text":"- with an audience","depth":13},{"id":16,"text":"made up largely of young people -","depth":13},{"id":17,"text":"the centerpiece of the president ' s visit .","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"\" The speech , \"","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"Mr. Sachs says ,","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"\" is the vehicle","depth":12},{"id":21,"text":"for the president","depth":12},{"id":22,"text":"to make his reintroduction \" to a skeptical Israel .","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"Israelis ,","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"who never embraced Obama the way","depth":12},{"id":25,"text":"many other audiences around the world did ,","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"have never quite forgiven this American president","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"for putting nearby Cairo on the list of sites for his first term ' s signature global issues speeches","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"- without even making a stop in Israel .","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"But Obama , with a speech","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"that warms up his image among Israelis ,","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"would be able to win not just popularity points , but even critical support for US initiatives in the region ,","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"Sachs says .","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"\" For the Israelis , it ' s not , ' What have you done for me lately , '","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"it ' s ' Do you love me ? ' \"","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"he says .","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"Further evidence","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"that Obama is out to redefine Israelis ' impression of him","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"comes from two of the iconic Israeli sites","depth":7},{"id":39,"text":"he will visit on his trip :","depth":7},{"id":40,"text":"the exhibit of the Dead Sea scrolls ,","depth":7},{"id":41,"text":"which is seen as Obama ' s recognition of the Jewish people ' s roots in Israel ;","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"and the grave of Zionist visionary Theodor Herzl .","depth":6},{"id":43,"text":"Both stops are aimed at correcting the impression","depth":5},{"id":44,"text":"left from Obama ' s Cairo speech","depth":6},{"id":45,"text":"that he sees Israel ' s creation as the result of the Holocaust rather than a millennia-old right to ancient Jewish lands .","depth":6},{"id":46,"text":"Obama is \" bound to get a bounce \" in Israel from his public diplomacy offensive ,","depth":5},{"id":47,"text":"Sachs says ,","depth":5},{"id":48,"text":"adding","depth":6},{"id":49,"text":"that improved public views of Obama could make a difference down the road .","depth":6},{"id":50,"text":"\" The Israeli public will punish a prime minister","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"who has a poor relationship with a popular American president , \"","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"he says .","depth":7},{"id":53,"text":"Thus a more popular Obama could lead to \" a more pliant Netanyahu , \"","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"he adds ,","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"for example on issues","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"related to the Israeli-Palestinian conflict .","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"The sense","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"that Obama ' s trip is really more about improving the climate for future initiatives","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"than about setting down an ambitious agenda","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"is prominent in White House pre-trip commentary .","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"\" There are obviously going to be significant decisions in the months and years ahead about Iran , about Syria , about Israeli-Palestinian peace , \"","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"says Ben Rhodes , deputy national security adviser for strategic communications .","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"Discussions","depth":13},{"id":64,"text":"Obama will have with Israeli and other leaders","depth":13},{"id":65,"text":"\" can frame those decisions","depth":13},{"id":66,"text":"that ultimately will come down the line , \"","depth":13},{"id":67,"text":"he says .","depth":11},{"id":68,"text":"\" That 's the way","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"in which the president is approaching the trip . \"","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"The perception","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"of tilling the ground for the future","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"is echoed by regional analysts .","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"\" This is a down-payment trip , \"","depth":10},{"id":74,"text":"says Aaron David Miller , vice president for new initiatives at the Woodrow Wilson International Center for Scholars in Washington .","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"\" If Obama ' s stock goes up","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"[ as a result of the visit ]","depth":12},{"id":77,"text":"in the eyes of the Israeli public ,","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"it will put additional pressure on Netanyahu . \"","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"The perception","depth":9},{"id":80,"text":"that Obama aims to make incremental progress with this trip","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"- while laying the groundwork for a potentially brighter horizon -","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"also applies at the regional level ,","depth":8},{"id":83,"text":"others say .","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"\" This trip is about managing Middle East problems ,","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"not solving them , \"","depth":9},{"id":86,"text":"says Haim Malka , deputy director of the Middle East program at the Center for Strategic and International Studies","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"( CSIS )","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"in Washington .","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"Whether the issue is Iran or Syria or the Israeli-Palestinian conflict ,","depth":9},{"id":90,"text":"Obama is visiting the region with no answers in his pocket","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"but with an eye on keeping any of a number of crises from spinning out of control ,","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"Mr. Malka and other analysts say .","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"Iran is certain to be topic No . 1 for Prime Minister Netanyahu .","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"Obama will underscore his view ,","depth":12},{"id":95,"text":"which he laid out to Israeli television last week ,","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"that there is still a \" window \" for an international diplomatic effort","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"to resolve concerns about Iran ' s uranium enrichment program .","depth":12},{"id":98,"text":"Yet","depth":13},{"id":99,"text":"even as Obama argues","depth":14},{"id":100,"text":"that diplomacy","depth":16},{"id":101,"text":"backed up by sanctions","depth":16},{"id":102,"text":"deserves more time ,","depth":15},{"id":103,"text":"the Israeli leader \" will try to convince Obama","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"that only threatening the use of force \"","depth":15},{"id":105,"text":"to stop Iran ' s nuclear progress","depth":16},{"id":106,"text":"- and meaning it -","depth":16},{"id":107,"text":"will have an impact on the Iranians ,","depth":14},{"id":108,"text":"Malka says .","depth":11},{"id":109,"text":"And","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"while the civil war in Syria may not get top billing ,","depth":12},{"id":111,"text":"the gravity of the violence and the growing regional implications of the two-year-old conflict are quickly moving Syria up on the regional agenda ,","depth":12},{"id":112,"text":"some experts say .","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"\" Syria is quite frankly the most burning issue","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"they","depth":13},{"id":115,"text":"[ Obama and Netanyahu ]","depth":13},{"id":116,"text":"have on the table","depth":13},{"id":117,"text":"to discuss , \"","depth":13},{"id":118,"text":"says David Ottoway , a senior scholar at the Wilson Center .","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"\" If this is a year of diplomacy toward Iran ,","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"it is also a year","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"of trying to decide when and if the US and Israel are going to intervene \" in Syria","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"to safeguard and stop the transfer of chemical weapons ,","depth":12},{"id":123,"text":"he says .","depth":9},{"id":124,"text":"Nor is Obama expected to lay out any new initiative","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"for advancing the goal of a \" two-state solution \" to the Israeli-Palestinian conflict .","depth":11},{"id":126,"text":"One reason is that Obama ' s \" fingers were burnt \"","depth":12},{"id":127,"text":"when he last tried to nudge the peace process along ,","depth":12},{"id":128,"text":"says Martin Indyk , a former US ambassador to Israel","depth":12},{"id":129,"text":"who is now director of the foreign policy program at Brookings .","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"But","depth":11},{"id":131,"text":"even if Obama was inclined to kick-start the peace process with a renewed effort ,","depth":13},{"id":132,"text":"the two sides in the conflict simply aren ' t ready ,","depth":13},{"id":133,"text":"Ambassador Indyk and others say .","depth":12},{"id":134,"text":"Netanyahu has just cobbled together a new coalition government","depth":13},{"id":135,"text":"( after January elections )","depth":13},{"id":136,"text":"that is largely focused on domestic economic and social issues .","depth":12},{"id":137,"text":"And the Palestinians remain deeply divided between Fatah and Palestinian Authority President Mahmoud Abbas in the West Bank , and Hamas in Gaza .","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"Obama will make the short trip from Jerusalem to Ramallah in \" the Beast , \" the president ' s armored limousine ,","depth":10},{"id":139,"text":"to meet with President Abbas on Thursday .","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"But Obama won ' t even attempt a charm offensive with the Palestinian public ,","depth":10},{"id":141,"text":"instead making some time in his Ramallah schedule","depth":11},{"id":142,"text":"to meet informally with a group of Palestinian youths .","depth":11},{"id":143,"text":"The president ' s last stop on a four-day trip will be Jordan","depth":6},{"id":144,"text":"- and there again , there ' s a strong sense","depth":7},{"id":145,"text":"that the visit is more about preparing for the \" significant decisions \" of the future","depth":8},{"id":146,"text":"than about solving problems today .","depth":8},{"id":147,"text":"Obama will meet with King Abdullah , one of America ' s closest Arab partners","depth":6},{"id":148,"text":"- but one","depth":8},{"id":149,"text":"whose country is increasingly feeling the weight of the Syrian refugee crisis .","depth":8},{"id":150,"text":"The growing humanitarian crisis only adds to tensions in Jordan over a struggling economy and steady","depth":9},{"id":151,"text":"- but by many accounts insufficient -","depth":9},{"id":152,"text":"political reforms .","depth":8},{"id":153,"text":"Get the Monitor Stories","depth":5},{"id":154,"text":"you care about","depth":5},{"id":155,"text":"delivered to your inbox .","depth":4},{"id":156,"text":"By signing up ,","depth":4},{"id":157,"text":"you agree to our Privacy Policy","depth":4},{"id":158,"text":"By visiting Jordan ,","depth":5},{"id":159,"text":"Obama is signaling","depth":7},{"id":160,"text":"that he wants to include in his trip an Arab country","depth":8},{"id":161,"text":"that the US foresees as a partner","depth":9},{"id":162,"text":"in addressing the region ' s issues ,","depth":9},{"id":163,"text":"analysts say","depth":6},{"id":164,"text":"- and these days Jordan may have stood out as his least problematic option .","depth":4},{"id":165,"text":"Underscoring how things have changed in the Middle East","depth":5},{"id":166,"text":"since Obama gave his Cairo speech in May 2009 ,","depth":5},{"id":167,"text":"CSIS ' s Malka says ,","depth":5},{"id":168,"text":"\" It would be way too complicated for the president to wade into Egypt at the moment . \"","depth":5}],"relations":[{"parent":337,"left":321,"right":336,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":321,"left":214,"right":320,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":214,"left":204,"right":213,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":204,"left":171,"right":203,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":171,"left":0,"right":170,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":170,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":203,"left":177,"right":202,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":177,"left":173,"right":176,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":173,"left":3,"right":172,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":172,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":176,"left":175,"right":9,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":175,"left":6,"right":174,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":174,"left":7,"right